      "content": "The Circle of Fifths is a map of the musical world, a giant, swirling wheel where every note is a tiny, distinct little creature with its own personality and favorite song. Imagine a giant, spinning wheel with twelve distinct sections, each representing a key. As you move clockwise, you skip a note and move to the next key, just like a goblin skipping a step on a playground while chasing a butterfly.\n\nHere is how you use it to figure out what key a song is in:\n\nFirst, find the key of **C Major** (or its relative minor, **A Minor**) at the very bottom of the wheel. This is your starting point, the \"home base\" of the circle. Now, pick a key you already know, like **F Major**. Look at the key of F Major on the wheel. If you move one step clockwise, you land on **G Major**. If you move another step, you hit **A Major**.\n\nThe magic happens when you move **counter-clockwise**. If you start at **G Major** and move one step counter-clockwise, you land on **E Major**. This is the reverse of the circle, like a goblin running in the opposite direction of the",
